snippet.textDisplay: From what I've read, West Coast Costumes didn't fix the cars. They just pimped it out. MTV producers stuck the people in this empty house and forced them to embellish a lot, made them sign NDA's, Cars usually took longer than the show portrays, many of the cars were sold afterwards because they didn't work and it became hard to maintain. It's interesting because Pimp My Ride was one of those shows I watched for the hell of it back in those days, we had a feeling it was too good to be true. Now that those days are long gone, it's cool and frustrating to know the behind the scenes of this show.
